{"word":"G5351 - φθείρω - phtheírō - fthi'-ro - Corrupt","slug":"G5351","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">φθείρω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>phtheírō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>fthi'-ro"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Corrupt"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03C6;&#x03B8;&#x03B5;&#x03B9;&#x0301;&#x03C1;&#x03C9; - phtheiro&#x0304;</b> - <i>fthi'-ro</i><p/>Probably strengthened from <b>&#x03C6;&#x03B8;&#x03B9;&#x0301;&#x03C9;</b> <b>phthio&#x0304;</b> (to <i>pine</i> or <i>waste</i>): properly to <i>shrivel</i> or <i>wither</i>, that is, to <i>spoil</i> (by any process) or (genitive) to <i>ruin</i> (especially figuratively by moral influences, to <i>deprave</i>): - corrupt (self), defile, destroy."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G1311\">G1311</a>, <a href=\"#/G1312\">G1312</a>, <a href=\"#/G2704\">G2704</a>, <a href=\"#/G5256\">G5256</a>, <a href=\"#/G5349\">G5349</a>, <a href=\"#/G861\">G861</a>, <a href=\"#/G862\">G862</a>, <a href=\"#/G90\">G90</a>"}]}